$interpreted: Tica: The source of the singing voice should be somewhere around here...
Tica: ...Is that!?
Tica: So she's the reason behind everything? It seems like she hasn't noticed me yet.
Tica: Alrighty! While she's busy minding her own business, I'll take her out in one fell swoop...
Tica: Gotcha!!!
Tica: Eh? Did it not work?
Tica: Darn it; don't be so full of yourself. I shall now show you my true power!
Tica: Whew~ It's finally over. I have to admit; you're a very worthy opponent.
Tica: The heck!? How are you still alive!?
Tica: Wait! I'm still not prepared...
Tica: Hey, where are you going? Don't ignore me!
Tica: Huh, weird. She's different from other marionettes. Doesn't go after me...
Tica: Hmm? What's this monument?
Tica: ... "Here lies Karl"...
Tica: Karl? Isn't that the name of the wandering boy?
Tica: The book said, "Until the day Karl died, the marionette never stopped singing"...
Tica: ...Does that mean you've been staying here by his side, singing to him all this time?
Tica: ...Also, you were giving off a white glow back there. It's different from the marionettes that attacked me; they had a black glow...
Tica: So the entire incident has nothing to do with you?
Tica: You only wanted to be by your master's side, right? I was so darn ignorant...I even attacked and injured you...
Tica: UGH! Stupid! Dumb! Idiot! I mean me!
Tica: However, if you're not the culprit, then why did those marionettes go nuts?
Tica: Eh? A dancing marionette?
Tica: Is it being attacked? But who's one doing it...
Tica: ...Is that black Soul Energy!?
Tica: Grrrr, so you're the true mastermind behind all this!
Tica: ...I-Isn't this a bit too~ much!?
